<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE42FF89FF0AFF615EA6FE3D" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFF615E97FEBD" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
Distribution. Palaearctic: From German to 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FCDFFF615F22FF7E" box="[782,868,175,201]" name="Poland" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Poland</collectingCountry>
. South Europe: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FBFAFF7E5838FF7D" box="[1067,1150,176,202]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FB5CFF615882FF7E" box="[1165,1220,175,201]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Italy</collectingCountry>
; Balkan region; Transcaucasia and Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD03FF015F6FFF5E" box="[722,809,207,233]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FCE4FF015F34FF5E" box="[821,882,207,233]" name="Syria" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Syria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FCAFFF1E5FF4FF5D" box="[894,946,208,234]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FC6DFF1E5FB7FF5D" box="[956,1009,208,234]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FC2AFF015882FF5D" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[1019,1220,207,234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref6810" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1987. A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Biologia 86. Prirodovedecka Fakulta, Univerzita J. E. Purkyne, Brne, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FF77FF215E8AFEBD" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." box="[166,716,239,266]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade Namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFEC15EA6FE3D" blockId="2.[166,1225,175,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
Biology. Only the morphological features of the egg and the first-instar larva have been described and figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FD8BFEE15EAFFEFD" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[602,745,303,330]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 300" refId="ref7413" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1989. Dipteres Sciomyzidae Euro-mediterraneens. Faune de France. France et Regions limitrophes. N ° 72. Federation Francaise de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles, Paris. 1 - 300." type="book chapter" year="1989">Vala (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. So, other information on the life cycle, developmental stages, and the prey remains lacking. This species appears univoltine and in 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FF77FEA15CB4FE3E" box="[166,242,367,393]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Russia</collectingCountry>
pupa are overwintering (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FDCBFEA15E93FE3D" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[538,725,367,394]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
